1
00:01:36,550 --> 00:01:39,009
[A Love Never Lost]

2
00:01:40,620 --> 00:01:42,009
[Episode 39]

3
00:01:47,400 --> 00:01:49,120
Your wife's face was so pale.

4
00:01:53,509 --> 00:01:54,530
Yeah.

5
00:01:57,300 --> 00:02:00,160
Our brother was living,
breathing, and energetic.

6
00:02:04,840 --> 00:02:06,480
And he's gone just like that.

7
00:02:08,940 --> 00:02:10,470
When Kaizhi died,

8
00:02:12,310 --> 00:02:14,060
were you at the scene or not?

9
00:02:22,090 --> 00:02:23,810
Are you suspecting me?

10
00:02:24,590 --> 00:02:25,630
Answer me.

11
00:02:27,420 --> 00:02:28,160
Were you

12
00:02:30,710 --> 00:02:32,110
there or not?

13
00:02:37,100 --> 00:02:38,900
Would you believe me if I said no?

14
00:02:40,730 --> 00:02:42,290
We're both well aware that

15
00:02:43,120 --> 00:02:44,870
only one person wanted Yang Kaizhi dead

16
00:02:44,870 --> 00:02:46,130
more than anyone else.

17
00:02:47,220 --> 00:02:49,220
That was your Mr. Yuan.

18
00:02:50,900 --> 00:02:51,490
Nope.

19
00:02:55,040 --> 00:02:57,040
If Kaizhi had succeeded and made

20
00:02:57,430 --> 00:02:58,560
the Sixth Division join forces

21
00:02:58,560 --> 00:02:59,750
with Zhang Shaozeng, Lan Tianwei,

22
00:02:59,750 --> 00:03:01,290
and Yan Xishan in Shanxi,

23
00:03:01,550 --> 00:03:02,570
upholding the uprising banner

24
00:03:02,570 --> 00:03:03,600
and marching straight to Beijing,

25
00:03:03,600 --> 00:03:05,110
would you, Liang Xiang, Liang Tufang,

26
00:03:05,110 --> 00:03:06,310
have tolerated that?

27
00:03:08,730 --> 00:03:10,730
Didn't you want to get rid of him too?

28
00:03:22,430 --> 00:03:23,280
That's true.

29
00:03:26,630 --> 00:03:28,710
Ever since I met Kaizhi,

30
00:03:30,290 --> 00:03:31,950
he had been living on the edge.

31
00:03:34,490 --> 00:03:35,750
After all these years,

32
00:03:38,160 --> 00:03:40,360
he still didn't let go of his obsession.

33
00:03:43,829 --> 00:03:45,600
What could we do about it?

34
00:03:47,590 --> 00:03:49,250
There was nothing we could do.

35
00:03:49,440 --> 00:03:51,020
I tried my best to persuade him,

36
00:03:51,020 --> 00:03:52,460
but he never listened.

37
00:03:58,310 --> 00:03:59,430
Actually...

38
00:04:02,870 --> 00:04:04,240
Actually, I knew this day

39
00:04:04,240 --> 00:04:05,770
would come sooner or later.

40
00:04:10,060 --> 00:04:11,620
I knew it long ago.

41
00:04:15,210 --> 00:04:17,050
I hinted to him so many times that

42
00:04:17,079 --> 00:04:19,459
he must abandon his ideals.

43
00:04:21,779 --> 00:04:22,630
He said

44
00:04:24,280 --> 00:04:25,760
he wasn't afraid of death.

45
00:04:28,840 --> 00:04:30,960
They're just that kind of people

46
00:04:34,190 --> 00:04:36,190
who'd rather sacrifice their lives

47
00:04:36,360 --> 00:04:39,000
than give up their lofty faith.

48
00:04:42,250 --> 00:04:43,960
If they're deprived of it,

49
00:04:47,960 --> 00:04:49,680
they won't survive even a day.

50
00:04:53,990 --> 00:04:55,870
You're so right.

51
00:04:59,750 --> 00:05:01,080
Yeah, that's it.

52
00:05:04,930 --> 00:05:06,990
Yang Kaizhi was fortunate, you know.

53
00:05:09,470 --> 00:05:10,910
He never gave up

54
00:05:10,940 --> 00:05:13,070
his pious belief till his last breath.

55
00:05:15,990 --> 00:05:17,460
Could you and I do that?

56
00:05:20,710 --> 00:05:22,460
Could you, Li Renjun, do that?

57
00:05:34,690 --> 00:05:36,080
Is it necessary?

58
00:05:40,159 --> 00:05:42,220
I, Li Renjun, live a simple life.

59
00:05:43,950 --> 00:05:44,950
Where there are benefits,

60
00:05:44,950 --> 00:05:46,680
you'll find me raking in money.

61
00:05:49,270 --> 00:05:50,950
So you switched sides to serve

62
00:05:50,950 --> 00:05:52,220
Mr. Yuan again, huh?

63
00:05:55,680 --> 00:05:57,460
Since my first day
in the Wuwei Corps Right Division,

64
00:05:57,460 --> 00:05:58,580
my heart

65
00:05:58,610 --> 00:06:00,590
has never betrayed him even once.

66
00:06:00,620 --> 00:06:03,150
What do you mean
by "switched sides to serve"?

67
00:06:07,110 --> 00:06:08,740
Then you bet on the right one.

68
00:06:17,190 --> 00:06:18,030
Tufang,

69
00:06:20,440 --> 00:06:22,710
let me speak from the bottom of my heart.

70
00:06:24,510 --> 00:06:26,040
The reason I came all the way to Beijing

71
00:06:26,040 --> 00:06:29,040
and hurried to your house
without going anywhere else

72
00:06:30,570 --> 00:06:32,520
was to tell you one thing.

73
00:06:41,630 --> 00:06:42,580
What's that?

74
00:06:47,430 --> 00:06:49,040
Be more flexible.

75
00:06:53,400 --> 00:06:55,710
We've already lost one brother.

76
00:06:57,760 --> 00:07:00,210
I, Li Renjun, don't want to lose you too.

77
00:07:07,880 --> 00:07:08,760
Flexible?

78
00:07:13,070 --> 00:07:14,630
How can I be flexible?

79
00:07:15,750 --> 00:07:16,680
You seriously still

80
00:07:16,680 --> 00:07:18,610
can't tell from the situation now?

81
00:07:19,310 --> 00:07:20,750
Who can save the world

82
00:07:20,750 --> 00:07:21,830
is already self-evident.

83
00:07:21,830 --> 00:07:23,710
Your Mr. Yuan again?

84
00:07:29,070 --> 00:07:30,290
Didn't Kaizhi's death

85
00:07:30,290 --> 00:07:32,530
hit you hard enough, Tufang?

86
00:07:36,110 --> 00:07:37,340
What do you mean?

87
00:07:43,270 --> 00:07:45,200
Be more flexible.

88
00:07:48,870 --> 00:07:50,659
You know what I mean.

89
00:07:56,510 --> 00:07:59,440
Brilliant talent draws
envy and the urge to destroy.

90
00:08:02,270 --> 00:08:05,470
A proud and unyielding spirit
finds no place in the world.

91
00:08:24,750 --> 00:08:27,070
By decree of the Empress Dowager.

92
00:08:27,630 --> 00:08:30,630
According to
the Prince Regent's personal report,

93
00:08:30,870 --> 00:08:32,630
it's been three years since he

94
00:08:32,870 --> 00:08:34,750
assumed the regency.

95
00:08:35,110 --> 00:08:39,240
His appointments and governance
have often gone against public opinion.

96
00:08:39,510 --> 00:08:41,870
The establishment of a constitution
ended up mere empty talk,

97
00:08:41,870 --> 00:08:43,870
causing abundant malpractices
and maladies,

98
00:08:43,870 --> 00:08:46,390
leading to the disintegration of people

99
00:08:46,390 --> 00:08:47,870
and the fall of national strength.

100
00:08:47,870 --> 00:08:50,030
One person's misguided measures

101
00:08:50,140 --> 00:08:53,510
caused terrible misfortune
to the entire nation.

102
00:08:53,870 --> 00:08:57,030
In deep grief and agony,
he found it too late to regret.

103
00:08:57,360 --> 00:08:59,390
If he continues to hold onto power

104
00:08:59,390 --> 00:09:00,870
and remains regent

105
00:09:01,030 --> 00:09:03,120
without considering stepping down,

106
00:09:03,360 --> 00:09:05,240
his imperial edicts won't work

107
00:09:05,510 --> 00:09:07,390
since he's lost people's trust.

108
00:09:07,550 --> 00:09:09,810
How can politics be expected to improve?

109
00:09:10,000 --> 00:09:11,600
He tearfully requests to resign

110
00:09:11,600 --> 00:09:13,840
from the position of Prince Regent

111
00:09:14,240 --> 00:09:17,000
and will no longer interfere
in state affairs.

112
00:09:19,120 --> 00:09:22,240
The Prince Regent is kind, gentle,

113
00:09:22,480 --> 00:09:24,150
cautious, and careful.

114
00:09:24,270 --> 00:09:26,270
Though his desire for good governance

115
00:09:26,270 --> 00:09:28,240
and his lack of flexibility

116
00:09:26,620 --> 00:09:30,870
[Emperor Xuantong, Aisin Gioro Pu Yi]

117
00:09:28,630 --> 00:09:30,630
has led to him being deceived and misled,

118
00:09:30,630 --> 00:09:32,230
bringing harm to the masses,

119
00:09:32,870 --> 00:09:34,870
his request should still be fulfilled.

120
00:09:32,930 --> 00:09:39,330
[Empress Dowager Longyu, Yehe Nara Jingfen]

121
00:09:35,030 --> 00:09:38,480
Approve his resignation
from the position of Prince Regent.

122
00:09:39,480 --> 00:09:42,390
The seal of the Prince Regent shall be

123
00:09:42,600 --> 00:09:44,600
returned and destroyed in no time.

124
00:09:44,790 --> 00:09:47,870
He shall return to his residence
as Prince Chun, with no more right

125
00:09:44,910 --> 00:09:48,270
[Prince Qing, President of Privy Council]
[Aisin Gioro Yi Kuang]

126
00:09:48,120 --> 00:09:49,850
to interfere in state affairs.

127
00:09:51,270 --> 00:09:54,550
He's awarded an annual salary
of 50,000 taels of silver,

128
00:09:55,030 --> 00:09:58,090
to be paid
from the imperial household expenses.

129
00:09:58,670 --> 00:10:00,870
Henceforth, appointments and governance

130
00:10:00,870 --> 00:10:04,120
shall be handled by the Prime Minister
of the Imperial Cabinet,

131
00:10:04,120 --> 00:10:07,920
with each minister being responsible
for their respective duties.

132
00:10:08,830 --> 00:10:11,850
[October 16, the third year of Xuantong
(December 6, 1911),]

133
00:10:11,850 --> 00:10:14,870
[the Prince Regent Zaifeng
abdicated at the age of 29.]

134
00:10:18,030 --> 00:10:19,360
As the dignified Prince Regent,

135
00:10:19,360 --> 00:10:20,620
the Emperor's father,

136
00:10:20,970 --> 00:10:23,170
he just threw in the towel and resigned,

137
00:10:23,200 --> 00:10:24,630
leaving behind such a perilous mess

138
00:10:24,630 --> 00:10:25,830
and staying out of it?

139
00:10:26,270 --> 00:10:27,080
He doesn't care about

140
00:10:27,080 --> 00:10:28,680
his people and his men at all!

141
00:10:29,410 --> 00:10:31,070
What the heck is this, Mother?

142
00:10:31,360 --> 00:10:32,030
Huh?

143
00:10:32,360 --> 00:10:33,490
How could he do that?

144
00:10:42,630 --> 00:10:45,240
Zaifeng's always been
such a good-for-nothing,

145
00:10:45,240 --> 00:10:46,630
not going anywhere.

146
00:10:47,510 --> 00:10:49,570
His resignation is not surprising.

147
00:10:51,870 --> 00:10:53,790
But our Empress Dowager Longyu

148
00:10:53,790 --> 00:10:55,390
was so autocratic this time.

149
00:10:55,750 --> 00:10:57,120
Not only did she not convene a meeting,

150
00:10:57,120 --> 00:10:58,030
but she also didn't consult

151
00:10:58,030 --> 00:11:00,230
with any lords from the imperial family

152
00:11:00,630 --> 00:11:02,290
before making that decision.

153
00:11:02,890 --> 00:11:04,640
She approved it within a day!

154
00:11:07,320 --> 00:11:08,240
She's even

155
00:11:08,240 --> 00:11:09,380
surpassed her aunt, Cixi,

156
00:11:09,380 --> 00:11:11,300
in boldness and decisiveness.

157
00:11:12,750 --> 00:11:13,870
How dare she act

158
00:11:13,870 --> 00:11:15,260
in Cixi's style?

159
00:11:17,510 --> 00:11:19,240
Does she really think

160
00:11:19,240 --> 00:11:20,900
she can be in charge?

161
00:11:21,150 --> 00:11:22,320
Anyone with a bit of sense

162
00:11:22,320 --> 00:11:23,910
wouldn't bring the disgrace of wrecking

163
00:11:23,910 --> 00:11:25,150
the whole country

164
00:11:25,150 --> 00:11:26,280
to his or her family.

165
00:11:28,200 --> 00:11:29,320
You mean

166
00:11:31,030 --> 00:11:32,320
Zaifeng saw the Qing dynasty

167
00:11:32,320 --> 00:11:33,520
heading to collapse,

168
00:11:34,020 --> 00:11:35,750
so he seized the chance to leave

169
00:11:36,130 --> 00:11:37,390
and avoid being blamed

170
00:11:37,890 --> 00:11:40,050
as the one causing the country's downfall?

171
00:11:40,050 --> 00:11:41,880
A hollowed-out great tree

172
00:11:43,630 --> 00:11:46,090
can't withstand even the slightest breeze.

173
00:11:47,280 --> 00:11:49,610
Zaifeng has been in power for three years,

174
00:11:49,980 --> 00:11:52,820
No way he doesn't know
how bad things have become.

175
00:11:54,510 --> 00:11:55,480
Son,

176
00:11:56,270 --> 00:11:57,750
listen to my advice.

177
00:12:00,360 --> 00:12:03,160
Don't meddle in affairs
that aren't our business.

178
00:12:03,750 --> 00:12:05,360
Zaifeng and his two brothers

179
00:12:05,750 --> 00:12:07,610
have all washed their hands of it.

180
00:12:07,670 --> 00:12:09,410
Why are you still trying to help?

181
00:12:09,410 --> 00:12:11,080
It's beyond your ability!

182
00:12:13,870 --> 00:12:14,550
Just let that

183
00:12:14,550 --> 00:12:16,550
shallow and vain woman take charge.

184
00:12:17,970 --> 00:12:19,960
Let's see what she, a widow,

185
00:12:21,110 --> 00:12:22,300
and her son can do.

186
00:12:26,630 --> 00:12:27,630
She, Longyu,

187
00:12:27,880 --> 00:12:29,390
is not Cixi.

188
00:12:30,240 --> 00:12:31,510
And Yuan Shikai

189
00:12:32,750 --> 00:12:34,870
is certainly not like Guangxu.

190
00:12:36,020 --> 00:12:37,450
Mother, you're right.

191
00:12:39,010 --> 00:12:40,440
Just today,

192
00:12:41,630 --> 00:12:43,830
she granted Yuan Shikai full authority

193
00:12:45,550 --> 00:12:48,080
to go negotiate with the revolutionary party

194
00:12:49,230 --> 00:12:50,540
in the south

195
00:12:51,870 --> 00:12:53,670
and discuss the bigger picture.

196
00:12:56,030 --> 00:12:57,050
Oh,

197
00:12:59,270 --> 00:13:01,150
our Qing dynasty, after two centuries

198
00:13:01,150 --> 00:13:02,480
of power and glory,

199
00:13:04,030 --> 00:13:06,630
there's no bigger picture
left for us anymore.

200
00:13:14,240 --> 00:13:16,150
As I've said before,

201
00:13:18,150 --> 00:13:20,350
we should see things through to the end.

202
00:13:23,670 --> 00:13:24,980
In our Liang family,

203
00:13:27,030 --> 00:13:29,150
we all stand on our own feet.

204
00:13:30,880 --> 00:13:31,790
Do your job

205
00:13:31,790 --> 00:13:33,380
within your duties.

206
00:13:35,980 --> 00:13:37,490
As for the rest,

207
00:13:44,410 --> 00:13:46,210
it's out of your control anyway.

208
00:13:51,510 --> 00:13:53,120
Just as you said, Mother,

209
00:13:55,510 --> 00:13:57,370
it's about to be out of my control.

210
00:13:59,750 --> 00:14:01,480
Yuan Shikai has already
reorganized his guards

211
00:14:01,480 --> 00:14:03,010
into the Defending Guards.

212
00:14:04,670 --> 00:14:06,800
They'll take over the responsibility

213
00:14:08,130 --> 00:14:09,760
for Beijing's security.

214
00:14:12,510 --> 00:14:13,790
The official handover ceremony

215
00:14:13,790 --> 00:14:15,250
will take place tomorrow.

216
00:14:16,930 --> 00:14:18,020
After that,

217
00:14:20,240 --> 00:14:22,150
the Imperial Guards will all be reassigned

218
00:14:22,150 --> 00:14:23,750
to station outside Beijing.

219
00:14:29,350 --> 00:14:30,380
I'm going to

220
00:14:32,260 --> 00:14:33,930
visit the Prince Regent later

221
00:14:35,240 --> 00:14:36,870
and settle things

222
00:14:38,730 --> 00:14:40,130
with him properly.

223
00:14:41,140 --> 00:14:41,930
Okay.

224
00:14:49,250 --> 00:14:50,760
Draw nicely,

225
00:14:50,870 --> 00:14:52,870
or Uncle Duanfang will scold you.

226
00:15:12,510 --> 00:15:13,510
Welcome back.

227
00:15:13,870 --> 00:15:15,030
But I have to leave soon.

228
00:15:15,030 --> 00:15:16,150
Puck up my

229
00:15:16,150 --> 00:15:16,720
daily items

230
00:15:16,720 --> 00:15:18,850
and have them loaded in the car. Hurry.

231
00:15:18,970 --> 00:15:20,210
Why such a rush?

232
00:15:45,230 --> 00:15:46,320
Here, take it.

233
00:15:51,270 --> 00:15:52,550
So what's going on?

234
00:15:53,210 --> 00:15:55,410
What assignment has Mr. Yuan given you?

235
00:15:57,530 --> 00:15:59,670
Brigade commander of the Defending Guards,

236
00:15:59,670 --> 00:16:01,360
responsible for guarding Beijing

237
00:16:01,360 --> 00:16:02,240
and ensuring

238
00:16:02,240 --> 00:16:03,550
Mr. Yuan's safety.

239
00:16:05,020 --> 00:16:06,820
That's a significant position.

240
00:16:08,630 --> 00:16:11,090
It's also a duty
assigned in times of crisis.

241
00:16:11,360 --> 00:16:12,550
The Imperial Guards in Beijing

242
00:16:12,550 --> 00:16:14,010
are feeling down and lost.

243
00:16:15,240 --> 00:16:17,140
I was asked to cooperate with Tufang

244
00:16:17,140 --> 00:16:18,850
to pacify the Imperial Guards

245
00:16:19,480 --> 00:16:20,880
in case of any accidents.

246
00:16:57,700 --> 00:16:59,510
Complete your last shift well tonight.

247
00:16:59,510 --> 00:17:00,040
Yes, sir.

248
00:17:19,200 --> 00:17:20,660
Come on, Pujie, come here.

249
00:17:32,030 --> 00:17:32,890
Your Highness.

250
00:17:37,470 --> 00:17:38,770
You came just in time.

251
00:17:41,130 --> 00:17:43,400
Light some incense for Duanfang as well.

252
00:17:46,460 --> 00:17:47,440
Mr. Duanfang?

253
00:17:50,550 --> 00:17:52,480
We've finally got confirmed news.

254
00:17:54,790 --> 00:17:55,680
Half a month ago, Duanfang

255
00:17:55,680 --> 00:17:57,080
was killed by the rebels.

256
00:17:57,860 --> 00:17:59,260
He died a terrible death.

257
00:18:09,750 --> 00:18:12,230
If I hadn't asked him
to come out of retirement,

258
00:18:12,230 --> 00:18:14,360
this tragedy wouldn't have happened.

259
00:18:16,830 --> 00:18:18,770
He was beheaded

260
00:18:19,090 --> 00:18:21,700
with his corpse dumped in the wilderness.

261
00:18:42,020 --> 00:18:42,970
How tragic.

262
00:18:45,340 --> 00:18:47,070
My son was still waiting for him

263
00:18:48,270 --> 00:18:50,270
to come back and teach him painting.

264
00:18:52,310 --> 00:18:53,310
Son?

265
00:18:54,810 --> 00:18:57,810
How come I've never heard you
mention your son before?

266
00:18:59,030 --> 00:18:59,830
Well, you were

267
00:19:00,950 --> 00:19:03,380
busy with countless state affairs,
Your Highness.

268
00:19:03,380 --> 00:19:07,310
Of course you had no time to listen
to a subordinate's domestic trivia.

269
00:19:08,960 --> 00:19:10,690
Now I have plenty of spare time.

270
00:19:14,790 --> 00:19:15,790
How are you doing?

271
00:19:17,270 --> 00:19:18,600
I heard from Zaitao that

272
00:19:19,070 --> 00:19:21,400
he left the messy affairs of settling down

273
00:19:22,420 --> 00:19:24,150
the Imperial Guards all to you.

274
00:19:25,810 --> 00:19:27,810
This is exactly what I came here for.

275
00:19:29,070 --> 00:19:30,400
I'm sorry to inform you,

276
00:19:30,960 --> 00:19:32,290
Your Highness, that your guards

277
00:19:32,290 --> 00:19:35,150
will be sent
to the Three Outer Battalions tomorrow.

278
00:19:35,150 --> 00:19:36,180
I will no longer

279
00:19:37,280 --> 00:19:38,410
be able to serve

280
00:19:40,100 --> 00:19:41,860
