00:25:50,620 --> 00:25:51,650
So you mean

357
00:25:53,890 --> 00:25:55,650
you know all the details?

358
00:25:59,030 --> 00:25:59,960
That's right.

359
00:26:01,130 --> 00:26:02,440
I know the details.

360
00:26:04,850 --> 00:26:07,450
Details are
the vivid expressions of history.

361
00:26:09,960 --> 00:26:12,270
When the gunshot rang out, I realized

362
00:26:13,170 --> 00:26:15,170
this was history taking its course,

363
00:26:15,870 --> 00:26:16,940
not entirely

364
00:26:16,960 --> 00:26:18,560
a conspiracy of anyone else.

365
00:26:19,420 --> 00:26:21,220
Everyone was held accountable,

366
00:26:22,600 --> 00:26:24,140
including Kaizhi himself.

367
00:26:29,360 --> 00:26:30,670
Your take

368
00:26:32,200 --> 00:26:33,490
is quite interesting.

369
00:26:36,240 --> 00:26:37,200
Do you think you, Tufang,

370
00:26:37,200 --> 00:26:38,600
bear no responsibility?

371
00:26:46,720 --> 00:26:47,550
Me?

372
00:26:49,640 --> 00:26:52,500
You knew he was a member
of the revolutionary party.

373
00:26:52,960 --> 00:26:54,030
You could have tried

374
00:26:54,030 --> 00:26:55,240
to stop his appointment.

375
00:26:55,240 --> 00:26:57,070
Even in the days before his death,

376
00:26:57,070 --> 00:26:57,830
you were still able

377
00:26:57,830 --> 00:26:59,110
to pull him back from the brink

378
00:26:59,110 --> 00:26:59,790
of death.

379
00:27:01,270 --> 00:27:02,960
But you didn't do so.

380
00:27:05,030 --> 00:27:07,430
You needed him to stay in the Sixth Division

381
00:27:07,580 --> 00:27:09,840
